        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/ecowas-coups-political-instability-west-africa.jpg" alt="Coups and attempted putsches have rocked nearly half of the original ECOWAS countries in the last decade" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          Coups and attempted putsches have rocked nearly half of the original ECOWAS countries in the last decade. Credits: International Crisis Group</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        ECOWAS‚Äôs <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-spotlights-h1-1-50th-anniversary" target="_blank">50th anniversary</a> comes at the worst moment, which was respected as a force for stability. The recent exits of Mali, Burkina Faso, and Niger, all of which were ‚Äã‚Äãunder military rule, have <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-spotlights-h1-2-hurt-its-credibility" target="_blank">hurt its credibility</a>. Rising jihadist <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-spotlights-h1-3-violence-in-the-sahel" target="_blank">violence in the Sahel</a> and Lake Chad regions has worsened tensions between member states. Countries like Nigeria and Benin are experiencing an increase in attacks.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      Trade issues show the impact of this turmoil. Traders from Nigeria <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-spotlights-h1-4-face-fivefold-tariff" target="_blank">face fivefold tariff</a> increases when exporting to Niger. This fuels smuggling and economic strain. ECOWAS Commission Chief Omar Touray noted the rising geopolitical pressures and economic uncertainty, while urging greater cooperation.</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Retired General Yakubu Gowon, a founder of ECOWAS, hopes the breakaway countries will return to the fold. He points to their shared culture and history. However, experts say the bloc‚Äôs leadership is weak. The original vision of unity is being threatened by political instability and a decline in democratic norms.</p>
