          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">
         Student visa crackdowns</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
         Summary: The Trump administration is targeting Chinese students amid its crackdown on universities.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The US <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-spotlights-h2-5-plans-to-revoke-visas" target="_blank">plans to revoke visas</a> for Chinese students. They also plan to revise visa criteria to enhance the scrutiny of all future visa applications from the People‚Äôs Republic of China and Hong Kong. Secretary of State Marco Rubio stated the revocations will target students linked to the Chinese Communist Party or those in ‚Äúcritical fields.‚Äù
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       China has condemned this policy, calling it discriminatory and politically driven. They warn it could harm ties and student exchanges. China was the top source of international students in the US for 15 straight years until it was surpassed by India just last year. This decision follows a recent truce in the ongoing trade dispute and reflects rising mistrust between the two nations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Rubio‚Äôs statement on Wednesday did not specify what the ‚Äúcritical fields‚Äù are, raising more questions. Washington is concerned about Chinese academics accessing sensitive and military-applicable American technology.</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Meanwhile, many Chinese students are afraid of deportation or not being able to finish their studies. Experts warn that this policy might cut one of the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-spotlights-h2-6-last-meaningful-links" target="_blank">last meaningful links</a> between the countries. Critics also question the unclear criteria for the visa revocations, noting the Communist Party's strong presence in Chinese society.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
