        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá´üá∑ France - To recognize Palestine.</strong> French President Emmanuel Macron reaffirmed support for a two-state solution to the Israel-Palestinian conflict, denying any double standards in France‚Äôs Middle East policy. He said France and Saudi Arabia will host a Gaza-focused conference in New York to boost efforts toward recognizing both a Palestinian state and Israel‚Äôs right to peace and security (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-worldwide-8-france-joining-the-club" target="_blank">France joining the club</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáµüá∞ Pakistan - Aiming for good PR.</strong> Pakistan is launching a diplomatic campaign to counter India‚Äôs global accusations of terrorism following the Pahalgam attack. PM Shehbaz Sharif, accompanied by top officials, is touring key allies to promote Pakistan as a peaceful and responsible nation (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-worldwide-9-pr-facelift" target="_blank">PR facelift</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá®üáø Czech Republic - Chinese ambassador summoned.</strong> The Czech Republic summoned China‚Äôs ambassador over cyberattacks, which were linked to China‚Äôs Ministry of State Security. The attacks targeted the Foreign Ministry since 2022. China denied involvement, calling the accusations politically motivated (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-worldwide-10-czech-s-beef" target="_blank">Czech‚Äôs beef</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáÆüá± Israel - Announces newer settlements.</strong> 
           Israel announced the creation of 22 settlements in the occupied West Bank. FM Bezalel Smotrich said it aims to block a Palestinian state. The plan drew sharp criticism from Hamas, Jordan, and others, who warned it would undermine peace and further entrench Israel‚Äôs occupation of Palestinian land (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-worldwide-11-more-about-the-plans" target="_blank">more about the plans</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá∑üá∫ Russia - Halt NATO enlargement.</strong> 
            Putin is demanding a written pledge from Western powers to halt NATO‚Äôs expansion and lift some sanctions to end the Ukraine war. Russia insists on Ukraine's neutrality, protection for Russian speakers, and the resolution of frozen assets (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-worldwide-12-putin-s-demands" target="_blank">Putin‚Äôs demands</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáÆüá∑ Iran - Trucker strike.</strong> 
            Iranian truckers have been on a strike for a week despite arrests by authorities. Drivers demand better working conditions, higher freight expenses, and relief from fuel restrictions. IRGC vehicles are reportedly transporting goods to break the strike (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-may-25-worldwide-13-more-about-the-strikes" target="_blank">more about the strikes</a>).
          </p>
